Iran Opposition Leader May Have Been Detained, N.Y. Times Says

-- B y   G r e g   C h a n g
-- 
2011-02-18T20:25:33Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-18/iran-opposition-leader-may-have-been-detained-n-y-times-says.html
Mir Hussein Mousasavi, a leader of  Iran ’s political opposition, is unable to be reached and may
have been detained, the New York Times reported, citing comments
the leader’s daughters made to an opposition website.   The daughters said that both parents have been unable to be
reached since Feb. 15 and that their home has been surrounded by
security forces, according to the report.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Greg Chang at 
 gchang1@bloomberg.net  